This is the “Sounds American” channel.

3
00:00:09,960 --> 00:00:14,860
In this video we’re going to talk about
the American vowel sound /ʌ/,

4
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,120
as in the word “us”.

5
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,220
You can also hear this sound in words like

6
00:00:22,240 --> 00:00:23,040
“but,”

7
00:00:23,280 --> 00:00:24,380
“come,”

8
00:00:24,580 --> 00:00:25,680
“young,”

9
00:00:25,740 --> 00:00:27,280
or “flood”.

10
00:00:28,080 --> 00:00:33,420
Please, note that we’ll be using a special phonetic symbol - /ʌ/ - for this sound.

11
00:00:34,900 --> 00:00:40,320
The vowel /ʌ/ exists in only 5% of the world’s languages.

12
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:47,780
It’s no wonder that non-native English speakers often distort it or replace it with more familiar sounds.

13
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:53,440
This video will help get you acquainted with the /ʌ/ and help you make it the right way.

14
00:00:53,700 --> 00:00:57,080
Let’s find out how to make this sound.

15
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:57,760
OK.

16
00:00:58,160 --> 00:01:03,600
To make the /ʌ/ sound, you should focus on the correct position of your lips and tongue.

17
00:01:04,200 --> 00:01:10,520
Open your mouth a little, relax your lips, and put them in a neutral position.

18
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:19,800
Place your tongue in the middle of your mouth, not too high or too low.

19
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:30,040
Note that the /ʌ/ vowel sound is used in stressed syllables, but your lips and tongue should not be tense.

20
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:33,440
Your tongue should be in the center of your mouth.

21
00:01:35,860 --> 00:01:37,900
Let’s try saying it:

22
00:01:38,740 --> 00:01:39,740
/ʌ/

23
00:01:41,360 --> 00:01:42,320
/ʌ/

24
00:01:43,740 --> 00:01:44,680
/ʌ/

25
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:50,560
Now, let’s practice this sound in some words.

26
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:54,220
