You’re done!

32
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,880
Congratulations!

33
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:24,420
By the way, the letter "u" stands for the /ʌ/ sound in 78% of cases.

34
00:04:25,180 --> 00:04:27,340
More on the spelling:

35
00:04:28,040 --> 00:04:34,160
Most often, the /ʌ/ sound is written as the letter “u,” as in the word “but,”

36
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:38,300
then as the letter “o,” as in the word “come.”

37
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:45,300
Less often it’s represented by the combination of the letters “ou,” as in the word “young,”

38
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:49,060
and “oo,” as in the word “flood.”

39
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,120
Thanks for watching!

40
00:04:56,460 --> 00:04:59,020
Hope you find it useful.

41
